		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_EVENT_AZTEC_UE_DESCRIPTION">
			<Text>What Has Been Set In Motion</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_EVENT_AZTEC_UE_HELP">
			<Text>Great Emperor, feathered serpent watch over you. The elder speakers have gathered to discuss these latest developments, as was requested.[NEWLINE][NEWLINE]When can they expect your presence?</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_EVENT_AZTEC_UE_HELP_CHOICE_1">
			<Text>Receive a Great Person of your choice.</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_EVENT_AZTEC_UE_HELP_CHOICE_2">
			<Text>The sacrifice of criminals generates +4 [ICON_PEACE] Faith and +4 [ICON_PRODUCTION] in Courthouses.</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_EVENT_AZTEC_UE_HELP_CHOICE_3">
			<Text>Discover new philosophical concepts using {1_YieldCost}. All Cities generate [ICON_GREAT_WRITER] Great Writers 20% faster. Writers' Guilds generate +1 [ICON_PEACE] Faith for every City.</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_EVENT_AZTEC_UE_HELP_CHOICE_4">
			<Text>Haciendados are given control over your Plantations: -2 [ICON_GOLD] Gold, but +2 [ICON_PRODUCTION] Production and +2 [ICON_FOOD] Food.</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_EVENT_AZTEC_UE_HELP_CHOICE_5">
			<Text>Invest {1_YieldCost} in a Rurales. A Fusilier spawns near every City and [ICON_STRENGTH] Crime thresholds are reduced by 15%.</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_EVENT_AZTEC_UE_HELP_CHOICE_6">
			<Text>Leverage {1_YieldCost} to popularise the Day of the Dead celebrations. Enter {4_Turns} of WLTKD. Holy Sites provide +3 [ICON_CULTURE] Culture, [ICON_TOURISM] Tourism and [ICON_FOOD] Food.</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_EVENT_AZTEC_UE_DESCRIPTION_CHOICE_1">
			<Text>Excellent. We gather to apoint a new tlatoani.</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_EVENT_AZTEC_UE_DESCRIPTION_CHOICE_2">
			<Text>*There are questions about whether or not our conquests are properly incorporating into our Empire*[NEWLINE]Those in violation of our laws will be treated like the capitves they are!</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_EVENT_AZTEC_UE_DESCRIPTION_CHOICE_3">
			<Text>*Our senior religious figures are pushing for stronger controls over our artists*[NEWLINE]Clearly, only art that expresses the nature of the teotl is any good. We must cultivate the minds of our citizens if we are to strengthen the faith.</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_EVENT_AZTEC_UE_DESCRIPTION_CHOICE_4">
			<Text>*The tlatoani are suggesting a devolution of state control to land owners*[NEWLINE]While this will reduce the revenues of our Cities, we can expect the creativity of our people to win out.</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_EVENT_AZTEC_UE_DESCRIPTION_CHOICE_5">
			<Text>*There are serious concerns over levels of crime around our growing Cities*[NEWLINE]We shall organise a militia to oppose this new wave of defiance.</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_EVENT_AZTEC_UE_DESCRIPTION_CHOICE_6">
			<Text>*People are losing respect in the traditional way of life*[NEWLINE]Blasphemy. We might not be ripping peoples hearts out anymore, but that doesn't mean we can forget our dead. We must organise a great celebration, in the style of the old ways.</Text>
		</Row>

		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_BUILDING_AZTEC_UE_DUMMY">
			<Text></Text>
		</Row>
	</Language_en_US>
</GameData>